UAC Foods Limited, makers of the Supreme ice cream brand, has unveiled a new logo, label, and an upgraded tub colour for the Supreme ice cream. While delivering his keynote address at the unveiling ceremony, the Managing Director of UAC Foods Limited, Mr Dele Ajayi, explained that Supreme ice cream was committed to supplying Nigerians and the world with high-quality and nourishing products. He said, “Since inception, UAC has been committed to supplying Nigerians and the world with high-quality products that provide our consumers with the nourishment they need. The vanilla, chocolate, and strawberry flavours of our Supreme Ice-cream brand show our unfailing dedication to provide unique and delicious ice cream to our beloved consumers.” The General Manager Marketing of UAC Foods Limited, Adebola Williams, who unveiled the new look and packaging of Supreme ice cream, said it depicts a celebration of life’s joyous moments. Also speaking, Brand Manager, Ponmile Alabi, expressed gratitude to key stakeholders who had contributed significantly to the growth of the organisation. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com